r($,"bXX","vd",()=>{var q="Full Time",p="Negotiable",o="assetss/images/cimage1.png",n="assetss/images/jobrequirements.png",m="assetss/images/cimage2.png",l="Any Graduation",k="Dubai",j="High-School",i="Camp Incharge",h="Cashier",g="Office Assistant",f="Business Consultant",e="Property Consultant",d="WNB Dubai is a premier Japanese restaurant chain with multiple locations across Dubai. Renowned for its authentic culinary experiences and exceptional service, WNB Dubai combines traditional Japanese flavors with modern dining aesthetics. Our commitment to quality and customer satisfaction makes WNB Dubai a standout choice for dining enthusiasts in the city.",c="Sales Executive",b="Sales Representative",a="High-school"
return A.a([A.l6("Admissions Officer","ATMS Education Group","AED3,500 - AED4,000 a month",q,"Bachelors Degree","Sharjah","2 years",p,"As strategic infrastructure partners for leading business schools and certification institutes, we aim to deliver top-quality education to students across the Middle East and beyond. With 17 years of experience, we have honed our expertise in empowering students for success.","The Admissions Officer will be responsible for making cold calls to new customers to shortlist and close business deals.",o,"\u27a4 Comfortable and confident in making 100+ Cold Calls and smart to identify the key decision-makers.\n\u27a4 Responsible to meet Daily/ weekly/ monthly targets.\n\u27a4 Must be able to explain and convince the prospects of the different academic programs we provide.\n\u27a4 Enquiry Management \u2013 counseling via emails, phone calls, and meetings;\n\u27a4 Collaborate with other departments for all relevant matters;\n\u27a4 Update and maintain a database of students\u2019 information;\n\u27a4 Organizing and filing of recruitment documentation;\n\u27a4 Performs miscellaneous job-related duties as assigned.\n\u27a4 Go the \u201cextra mile\u201d to meet enrolment targets and facilitate future enrolments industry",n,"\u27a4 Minimum 2 years of experience in sales and marketing in international markets.\n\u27a4 Preferably bachelor\u2019s degree holder\n\u27a4 Excellent command of both written and spoken English.\n\u27a4 Ability to develop and deliver presentations\n\u27a4 Proven record in telesales, sales, marketing, or customer service role.\n\u27a4 Proficient communicator, both oral and written\n\u27a4 Excellent organizational and coordination skills\n\u27a4 MS Applications proficiency and computer literacy\n\u27a4 Ability in handling objections with confidence.\n\u27a4 Knowledge of potential sales market.\n\u27a4 Must be comfortable and confident in making 100+ Cold Calls per day.\n\u27a4 Good team player within a multifunctional team\n\u27a4 Affinity with, and interest in educationt.",m,"Admission Officer","","",""),A.l6("Document Controller (Male)","Sobha LLC","AED 3,000 - 5,000",q,l,k,"1 - 4 Years",p,"Sobha Realty, headquartered in Dubai, specializes in delivering exceptional luxury residences at prestigious locations worldwide. Our commitment to quality and innovation is exemplified in projects like Sobha Hartland, a Dollar 4 billion development featuring 8 million square feet of community space with a focus on green areas, and Meydan Sobha, an Dollar 8 billion venture transforming 45 million square feet into an exclusive luxury destination. With a philosophy of no shortcuts to quality, Sobha Realty ensures every detail is meticulously crafted to create unparalleled living experiences.","We are hiring a full-time Document Controller for Sobha Realty in Dubai. This on-site role involves managing, organizing, and maintaining project documentation, ensuring accuracy and regulatory compliance. The Document Controller will communicate with internal teams and external stakeholders to facilitate efficient document flow and record management.",o,"\u27a4 This is a full-time on-site role for a Document Controller at Sobha Realty in Dubai.\n\u27a4 The Document Controller will be responsible for managing, organizing, and maintaining project documentation, ensuring accuracy, quality, and compliance with regulations.\n\u27a4 The role will involve communication with internal teams and external stakeholders to facilitate efficient document flow and record management.",n,"\u27a4 Document Management, Documentation, and Project Documentation skills\n\u27a4 Records Management and Communication skills\n\u27a4 Attention to detail and organizational skills\n\u27a4 Ability to work effectively in a team environment\n\u27a4 Proficiency in document control software\n\u27a4 Experience in the real estate or construction industry is a plus\n\u27a4 Bachelor's degree in a relevant field\n\u27a4 Should be excellent with Microsoft Excel",m,"Document Controller","","",""),A.l6("Office boy/ Cleaner","NETSOLE IT SOLUTIONS LLC","AED 2,000 - AED 2,500 a month",q,j,k,"Fresher",p,"Netsole IT Solutions LLC is a comprehensive IT service provider committed to delivering cost-effective and accessible IT support to individuals and businesses throughout the Middle East. With 12 years of experience, we ensure all your IT infrastructure needs are met with dedicated and expert solutions.","We are seeking a reliable Office Boy/Cleaner to maintain a clean and organized work environment. Responsibilities include daily cleaning and maintenance of office areas, handling office supplies, and assisting with general administrative tasks. The ideal candidate should have a strong work ethic, attention to detail, and the ability to follow instructions. Prior experience in a similar role is a plus.",o,"\u27a4 Maintain cleanliness and orderliness of the office premises, including desks, meeting rooms, kitchen and common areas.\n\u27a4 Serve tea, coffee, and refreshments to staff and guests.\n\u27a4 Assist with photocopying, filing, and distributing documents.\n\u27a4 Handle incoming and outgoing mail and packages.\n\u27a4 Monitor and maintain office supplies and inventory.\n\u27a4 Assist with minor clerical tasks as required.\n\u27a4 Perform duties as assigned by the office manager.",n,"\u27a4 Fresher is acceptablec, but experience will be preffered.",m,"House Cleaner","","",""),A.l6(i,"INTERGRANDE BKC GROUPS","AED2,000 - AED2,500 a month",q,j,"Sharjah","Minimum Experience",p,"With over 22 years of experience, Intergrande BKC offers a comprehensive range of manpower services throughout the United Arab Emirates, serving a diverse clientele in infrastructure, construction, factories, and interior fit-out sectors. We provide top-tier, customized manpower solutions to drive the success of UAE\u2019s leading companies.","We are seeking a Camp Incharge to develop and implement camp policies, supervise and train staff, ensure a safe and enjoyable environment for campers, adhere to health and safety regulations, manage budgets and resources, coordinate activities, monitor performance, liaise with parents and stakeholders, and maintain accurate records.",o,"\u27a4 Developing and implementing camp policies and procedures\n\u27a4 Supervising and training camp staff\n\u27a4 Maintaining a safe and enjoyable environment for campers\n\u27a4 Ensuring health and safety regulations are adhered to\n\u27a4 Managing budgets and resources\n\u27a4 Organising and coordinating camp activities\n\u27a4 Monitoring and evaluating camp performance\n\u27a4 Liaising with parents and other stakeholders\n\u27a4 Maintaining accurate record-keeping",n,"\u27a4 Language:\nHindi (Required)",m,i,"","",""),A.l6(h,"Lune Lounge Cofee","AED1,500 - AED2,000 a month",q,"High-School ",k,"1 year",p,"Lune Lounge Coffee is a vibrant and stylish caf\xe9 located in Jumeirah 2, Dubai. Known for its specialty coffees and delectable signature desserts, Lune Lounge offers a unique dining experience with a view of the iconic Burj Khalifa. The caf\xe9 features multiple seating areas, including indoor spaces, a rooftop terrace, and a garden, creating the perfect ambiance for both daytime coffee dates and evening gatherings. With its combination of modern aesthetics and traditional coffee culture, Lune Lounge has become a popular spot for coffee enthusiasts and casual diners alike in Dubai.","Lune Lounge Coffee is seeking a dedicated and customer-focused Cashier to join our team. As a Cashier, you will be the first point of contact for our guests, ensuring a warm welcome and efficient service. Your primary responsibilities will include handling customer transactions, managing the cash register, and maintaining an organized checkout area. You will also assist in answering customer queries, providing information about our menu, and ensuring a pleasant overall experience for our guests. The ideal candidate will have excellent communication skills, a friendly demeanor, and the ability to work in a fast-paced environment. Previous experience in a similar role is preferred but not required.",o,"\u27a4 Abu Dhabi: \nReliably commute or planning to relocate before starting work (Required)",n,"\u27a4 Having at least one year of experience as a cashier is preferred for this position.",m,h,"","",""),A.l6("Holiday Homes Guest Relations Officer","Aurora Vacation Homes Rentals LLC","AED 6,000 - AED8,000 a month",q,l,k,"3 years",p,"Aurora is a premier holiday homes company situated in the heart of Dubai. We are dedicated to delivering impeccable short-term rental experiences, making every guest feel right at home while introducing them to the unique charm of Dubai","Operations & Management: Oversee the daily operations of our holiday homes, ensuring properties are in pristine condition and meet Aurora's high standards.\nGuest Relations: Act as the primary contact for guests. Assist them with any requests, questions, or concerns before, during, and after their stay. Provide detailed information about our properties, services, and the local area. Handle complaints and issues, ensuring guest satisfaction and upholding the company's reputation. Keep records of guest interactions, transactions, comments, and complaints. Promote and upsell additional services and experiences offered by Aurora.\nBooking & Reservations: Manage all aspects of bookings using property management software and ensure smooth check-ins and check-outs.\nFeedback Handling: Monitor guest feedback, address concerns promptly, and implement measures to improve guest satisfaction.\nTeam Collaboration: Work closely with housekeeping, maintenance, and other teams to ensure the optimal guest experience. Schedule cleaning tasks for changeovers.",o,"\u27a4 Previous experience in holiday home management, guest relations, or a similar role in the hospitality sector. (preferred, but not required)\n\u27a4 Outstanding organizational, leadership, and customer service skills.\n\u27a4 Proficient in using property management software.\n\u27a4 Exceptional communication skills in English; knowledge of additional languages is a bonus.\n\u27a4 Familiarity with Dubai's attractions, culture, and local hotspots.\n\u27a4 Problem-solving attitude, with the ability to gracefully manage challenging situations.\n\u27a4 Flexible mindset, holiday homes business operates on a 24/7 basis. (day offs are provided)\n\u27a4 UAE driving license (required)\n\u27a4 Own car (preferred, but not required)",n,"\u27a4 Experience: Holiday Homes (in Dubai): 3 years (Required)\nLanguage:\n\u27a4 Arabic (Preferred)\nEnglish fluently (Required)\n\u27a4 License/Certification:\nUAE driving license (Required)\nLocation:\n\u27a4 Dubai (Required)",m,"Relations Officer","","",""),A.l6(g,"ALEKHTYAR ALAWAL TECHNICAL SERVICES","AED 4,000 \u2013 AED 5,000 a month",q,j,k,"Proven experience",p,"Landmark Hotels and Suites is a distinguished hospitality brand known for its exceptional service and luxurious accommodations. Strategically located in prime areas, our hotels and suites offer guests a perfect blend of comfort, elegance, and convenience. Whether traveling for business or leisure, guests at Landmark Hotels and Suites can expect a memorable and delightful stay, marked by top-notch amenities and personalized service.","We are looking for a competent Office Assistant to help with the organization and running of the daily administrative operations of the company.",o,"\u27a4 Proven experience as a back-office assistant, office assistant, virtual assistant or in another relevant administrative role\n\u27a4 Knowledge of \u201cback-office\u201d computer systems (ERP software)\n\u27a4 Working knowledge of office equipment\n\u27a4 Thorough understanding of office management procedures\n\u27a4 Excellent organizational and time management skills\n\u27a4 Analytical abilities and aptitude in problem-solving\n\u27a4 Excellent written and verbal communication skills\n\u27a4 Proficiency in MS Office",n,"\u27a4 Demonstrated experience as a back-office assistant, office assistant, virtual assistant, or in a comparable administrative role.",m,g,"","",""),A.l6(f,"Black Swan Business Setup Services","AED 3,000 - 10,000 per Month",q,"BBA",k,"0 - 5 Years",p,"Black Swan is a premier business formation company assisting locals and expats in incorporating their companies in Dubai and other Emirates. We provide customized, cost-effective solutions for businesses of all sizes, ensuring a quick and hassle-free start. Our supportive and approachable team is dedicated to client satisfaction, solving business-related issues with 100% transparency and accountability.","We are looking for a Company Formation Consultant / Corporate Sales to join our operations and customer service team at Black Swan business Set up Services.",o,"\u27a4 Leads Handling: \nIdentify, engage, and qualify prospects contacting the company and ensuring a healthy pipeline of potential clients interested in company formation, visa applications, and related services.\n\n\u27a4 Initial Consultation: \nServe as the first point of contact for potential clients, providing expert consultations to understand their needs, explain our services, and establish the value proposition.\n\n\u27a4 Sales Strategy Development: \nDevelop and implement effective sales strategies tailored to each potential client, focusing on their unique needs and how our services can meet those needs.\n\n\u27a4 Client Relationship Building: \nFoster strong relationships with prospective clients from the first touchpoint, demonstrating industry knowledge, professionalism, and the ability to understand and articulate client needs.\n\n\u27a4 Proposal and Pitch Creation: \nCraft compelling proposals and presentations that clearly outline the benefits of our services, the process involved, and the value it brings to the client.\n\n\u27a4 Negotiation and Closure: \nLead the negotiation process, effectively addressing any client concerns or objections, and drive the conversation towards a successful sale closure.\n\n\u27a4 Collaboration with Internal Teams: \nWork closely with internal teams to ensure proposed services are feasible and aligned with the company's capabilities and standards.\n\n\u27a4 Sales Pipeline Management: \nEfficiently manage the sales pipeline, ensuring timely follow-ups, keeping accurate records of interactions, and moving potential clients through the sales funnel towards closure.\n\n\u27a4 Feedback and Improvement: \nCollect feedback from potential clients, regardless of whether a sale is closed, to refine sales strategies, improve service offerings, and enhance client engagement techniques.",n,"\u27a4 Have some experience in Corporate Sales having sales cycle handling experience\n\u27a4 Immediate availability to join or a short notice joining date\n\u27a4 Experience in business setup, immigration or similar industries is not needed.\n\u27a4 Integrity and humility\n\u27a4 A collaborative team-player mindset\n\u27a4 The ability to multitask effectively",m,f,"","",""),A.l6(e,"Cotton & Wood International LLC","AED2,500 - AED6,500 a month",q,"Bachelor\u2019s Degree",k,"Real Estate: 1 year",p,"Cotton and Wood is a dynamic and leading player in the real estate industry, committed to providing exceptional services to our clients.","We are currently seeking a motivated and results-driven Telesales Representative to join our high-performing team. If you have a passion for real estate, excellent communication skills, and a proven track record in telesales, we want to hear from you",o,"\u27a4 Generate high-quality leads through outbound calls to potential clients.\n\u27a4 Qualify leads by understanding their real estate needs, budget, and timeline.\n\u27a4 Provide information on available properties, market trends, and real estate services.\n\u27a4 Work towards achieving individual and team sales targets.\n\u27a4 Guide clients through the real estate buying or selling process, closing deals effectively.\n\u27a4 Maintain accurate records of client interactions and sales activities in the CRM system.\n\u27a4 Stay informed about current real estate market trends and competitor offerings.",n,"\u27a4 High school diploma required; bachelor's degree in business, marketing, or a related field is a plus.\n\u27a4 Previous experience in telesales, customer service, or real estate sales is advantageous\n\u27a4 Own Visa is preferable\n\u27a4 HIndi /Urdu speaking female candidates would be prefered.",m,e,"","",""),A.l6("Receptionist (Female)","Zafco Group Holding Limited","AED 2,000 - 4,500  per month",q,l,k,"1 - 5 Years",p,d,"We are hiring a Receptionist to manage front desk operations, including answering and forwarding calls, scheduling appointments, and greeting visitors. Responsibilities include handling customer complaints, maintaining employee contact records, processing utility bills and travel arrangements, managing office supplies, and ensuring a clean and presentable reception area. The ideal candidate will also assist with HR and administrative tasks as needed.",o,"\u27a4 Answer, screen and forward calls, providing information, taking messages and scheduling appointments.\n\u27a4 Maintain contact details of employees and keep a current record of staff members' whereabouts and availability.\n\u27a4 Greet persons entering the establishment, determine nature and purpose of visit, and direct or escort them to specific destinations.\n\u27a4 Attends and resolves to customer/guest complaints\n\u27a4 Handover cheques to Aramex and related parties with proper monitoring.\n\u27a4 Handling office tasks, such as filing, generating reports as needed, and setting up for meetings,\n\u27a4 Ordering office supplies, ensuring all items are delivered on time and always available in stock.\n\u27a4 Arrange gate passes for the guests and employees as and when required.\n\u27a4 Process utility bill payments on time and always keep an updated record.\n\u27a4 Making travel arrangements, such as booking flights, hotel and restaurant reservations and managing all travel related documents / NOC's / Visa etc.\n\u27a4 Collect, sort, distribute and prepare mail, and courier shipment and process the payment.\n\u27a4 Ordering food for the guests and process for billing.\n\u27a4 Ensure the message display at reception\u2019s LED screen is updated as per the requirement.\n\u27a4 Always keeps the reception area clean and presentable.\n\u27a4 Perform other HR/Administrative duties that may be assigned from time to time",n,"\u27a4 Must have UAE Experience\n\u27a4 Must have Good Communication",m,"Receptionist","","",""),A.l6("Sales Associate (Female)","Beside Group",p,q,l,k,"0 - 3 Years",p,"Beside Group is the preferred partner for renowned international fashion brands including Diesel, Fred Perry, Pinko, Scotch & Soda, Puma, Geox, Longchamp, and Aape. Our Retail division manages stores across the UAE, KSA, Kuwait, Qatar, Bahrain, Oman, and Egypt.","We are looking for a Sales Associate to build and maintain strong customer relationships, drive sales, and achieve targets. Responsibilities include providing exceptional customer service, assisting with product selection, upselling and cross-selling, processing transactions, and keeping the sales floor organized. The ideal candidate will stay updated on product knowledge, support inventory management, and actively promote sales promotions while contributing to a positive team environment.",o,"\u27a4 Build and maintain strong relationships with customers to drive sales and achieve targets.\n\u27a4 Provide exceptional customer service and assist customers with product selection and inquiries.\n\u27a4 Actively engage in upselling and cross-selling to increase sales and maximize revenue.\n\u27a4 Stay updated on product knowledge, features, and benefits to effectively communicate with customers.\n\u27a4 Process customer transactions accurately and efficiently using the POS system.\n\u27a4 Maintain a clean and organized sales floor to enhance the customer shopping experience.\n\u27a4 Collaborate with team members to achieve sales goals and contribute to a positive work environment.\n\u27a4 Assist in inventory management, including restocking shelves and monitoring stock levels.\n\u27a4 Stay informed about current sales promotions and effectively promote and market products.\n\u27a4 Continuously seek opportunities for personal and professional growth to enhance sales skills and performance.",n,"\u27a4 High school diploma or equivalent education required, with a focus on business or sales preferred.\n\u27a4 Proven experience in a sales or customer service role, preferably in a retail environment.\n\u27a4 Strong knowledge of the industry and products being sold.\n\u27a4 Excellent communication and interpersonal skills to effectively engage with customers and build relationships.\n\u27a4 Results-oriented and driven to achieve sales targets and exceed customer expectations.\n\u27a4 Ability to work in a fast-paced and dynamic environment, with a flexible schedule including evenings and weekends.\n\u27a4 Ability to work effectively both independently and as part of a team.\n\u27a4 Attention to detail and accuracy in processing transactions and handling cash.\n\u27a4 Positive attitude, enthusiastic, and passionate about providing exceptional customer service",m,"Sales Associate","","",""),A.l6(c,"DRL Marketing Management","AED3,000 - AED4,000 a month",q,"Hindi (Required)",k,"Telesales: 1 year",p,"We provide expert support and promotional services to businesses of all sizes. Our dedicated team engages in direct communication with clients, presenting innovative business opportunities and advanced solutions to foster their growth.","We are looking for enthusiastic and dynamic Call Centre Agent sales professionals to join our team.",o,"\u27a4 Engage and convert new client leads into loyal customers, while following all regulatory standards.\n\u27a4 Educate customers about our products and services to spark interest in our brand.\n\u27a4 Turn customer inquiries into valuable sales opportunities.",n,"\u27a4 Skill Set: \nExceptional communication, creativity, patience, and a strong ability to engage and persuade customers.\n\u27a4 Readiness: \nWe value candidates who are eager to take on this role immediately.",m,c,"","",""),A.l6(b,"Aaramam","AED2,000 - AED2,500 a month ",q,a,k,"Sales: 1 year",p,"Aaraamam, a renowned Kerala restaurant in Dubai, is located at Belhasa Building near Shaika Hamdan Colony in Al Karama. Known for its unique charm and diverse menu, Aaraamam offers a rich selection of authentic Kerala coastal and regional dishes. Experience the true flavors of Kerala at our esteemed establishment.","We are looking to hire an experienced sales girl. Must have had experience in sales, preferably in the F&B industry. Would also required to be part time cashier.",o,"\u27a4 Must have their own accommodation in Karama",n,"\u27a4 We prefer candidates with at least one year of sales experience.",m,b,"","",""),A.l6("Waiter/Cashier","WNB Dubai","AED2,800 - AED3,000 a month",q,a,k,"Waiter: 1 year",p,d,"A Japanese restaurant with several locations in Dubai is seeking young, energetic, and passionate individuals to join our expanding team as Waiters/Cashiers.",o,"\u27a4 Reliably commute or planning to relocate before starting work (Required)",n,"\u27a4 Applicants for the waiter position must have a minimum of one year of relevant experience.",m,h,"","","")],t.LE)})
